    <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>
            What is Future Egg?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>Future Egg is a one stop shop for all of your do it yourself computer building needs.</li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            Do you price match other websites?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>No!</li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            Do you sell software?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Not yet.  But it is in the planning phases.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            What is your return policy?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                We accept returns on all products up to a month after purchase regardless of condition.
            </li>

        </ul>
        <li>
            Why would you advertise your competitor Newegg?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                We believe that even after shopping on our main competitors website people will come back to our store for their purchase.  We believe this because of our great customer support and prices.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            Do you only sell parts or are you also selling completely built computer rigs?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Right now we are only selling individual parts.  In the future this may change.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            What payment options do I have as a consumer?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                We accept all major credit cards as well as Bitcoin.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            What is your warrenty policy?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                We have a 1 month no questions asked policy on all of our products.  Extended full replacement warranties can be purchased for up to 2 years.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            Do you ship outside of the United States?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                For the foreseeable future we will only be shipping within the United States.  Sorry for the inconvenience.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <li>
            Do you offer any guides or have recommendations on compatible parts?
        </li>
        <ul>
            <li>
                We personally do not, however over at <a href="https://pcpartpicker.com/">PC Part Picker</a> you can compare every computer part to see if they are compatible.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </ul>
</asp:Content>

